                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13479905/comment/17599604",
                    "id": "17599604",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "Here's a reproducer just using Expressions, no dplyr:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nexpr <- Expression$create(\"multiply_checked\", Expression$field_ref(\"col1\"), Expression$field_ref(\"col2\"))\r\nexpr\r\n\r\n# Expression\r\n# multiply_checked(col1, col2)\r\n\r\nexpr$type(schema(col1=decimal128(33, 4), col2=decimal128(15, 2)))\r\n\r\n# Error: Invalid: Decimal precision out of range [1, 38]: 49\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nNote that the different kernels have different promotion logic. Subtraction, for example, doesn't go out of range with these types.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nexpr <- Expression$create(\"subtract_checked\", Expression$field_ref(\"col1\"), Expression$field_ref(\"col2\"))\r\nexpr$type(schema(col1=decimal128(33, 4), col2=decimal128(15, 2)))\r\n\r\n# Decimal128Type\r\n# decimal128(34, 4)\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
