                        },
                        "displayName": "Yibo Cai",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Hmm, there are some difficulties:\r\n- If the total digits of the two input decimal128 types to be multiplied is larger than 38, the output type cannot be represented by decimal128 without losing precision. It has to fail.\r\n- Decimal overlow, like floating points, should lead to {{Inf}}, whether checked or non-checked. Currently we don't support decimal {{Inf}}.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=yibocai",
                        "name": "yibocai",
                        "key": "yibo",
                        "avatarUrls": {
