                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "The trouble with the status quo is that we fail even if there is no overflow or required digits > 38:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n> one <- Array$create(1)$cast(decimal128(33, 0))\r\n> one\r\nArray\r\n<decimal128(33, 0)>\r\n[\r\n  1\r\n]\r\n> two <- Array$create(2)$cast(decimal128(33, 0))\r\n> one + two\r\nArray\r\n<decimal128(34, 0)>\r\n[\r\n  3\r\n]\r\n> one * two\r\nError: Invalid: Decimal precision out of range [1, 38]: 67\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
